canonical:
  title: 小雨
  author: 金時習
  language: lzh
  text: 天街小雨洒紛紛半作靑烟半作雲獨掩柴關人正靜一聲泥滑隔山聞
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 小雨
  author: 金時習
  language: lzh
  text: 天街小雨洒紛紛。半作靑烟半作雲。獨掩柴關人正靜。一聲泥滑隔山聞。
korean:
  title: 소우
  author: 김시습
  language: kor
  text: |-
    서울 거리에 보슬비가 어지러이 뿌리나니
    반은 푸른 연기 되고 반은 구름이 된다
    혼자 사립문 닫고 있으매 사람은 진정 고요한데
    한 소리 이활이 산 넘어서 들리네
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_1450_020_0630&viewSync=OT
  footnotes: []
english:
  title: Fine Rain
  author: Kim Siseup
  language: eng
  text: |-
    Fine rain scatters and drifts across the streets of Seoul,
    Half becoming wisps of azure smoke, half turning to cloud.
    Alone behind my brushwood gate, all falls silent—
    One slip of mud's whisper carries over the mountains.
  footnotes:
  - key: ''
    value: The 'brushwood gate' (사립문) suggests a humble, secluded dwelling, emphasizing the speaker's solitude and retreat from the world.
  - key: ''
    value: The final line captures how even the smallest sound—a footstep in mud—becomes magnified in the stillness, traveling across the landscape as if transformed by the rain.
